            {"question":"How is 'viability' specifically defined within the context of Egyptian obstetric practice?","options":["The onset of the third trimester at 27 weeks","The point at which the fetus reaches a weight of 500 grams","The completion of 24 weeks of gestation","The completion of 28 weeks of gestation"],"answer":"The completion of 28 weeks of gestation"},
