            {"question":"How do cervical effacement and dilatation differ between a primigravida and a multigravida?","options":["In a multigravida, effacement must be complete before dilatation begins","In a primigravida, they occur simultaneously","In a multigravida, dilatation occurs only after the fetus reaches the pelvic floor","In a primigravida, effacement occurs before dilatation"],"answer":"In a primigravida, effacement occurs before dilatation"},
